name: Wang's Shanghai Cuisine
address: Wang's Shanghai Cuisine, 3328 Kingsway #110, Vancouver, BC V5R 5L1

featured_reviews.review_id: This is a small and humble eatery, with many comforting dishes on the menu. The place is known for soup dumplings, pan fried dumplings, and spicy beef noodle soup. These are the three things I usually order. Noodles and dumplings are fresh tasting each time. Soup is just the right amount of spicy, and I like the beef. There isn't much sit down capacity, so be prepared to wait in line during prime times. Interior is what you'd expect from a small and authentic Asian eatery.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Lined up for 20 mins at the door (without shade ) to get in
The place is small and crowded with friendly staff
XLB was excellent very juicy and soupy
Wonton dumpling was ok with more veggie than meat but the dumpling wrapper was so  smoothy tasty! It suppose to come with 10 pcs but they gave me 9 first and told me one more coming and I appreciate their honesty
Portion of spicy noodle was quite small with a few pieces of meat only
The worse is the green onion pancake, dry, tasteless , hard and look aged
Overall with this price range for Shanghai food definitely worth a try!

featured_reviews.review_id: Funny story, we went to this area because we bought pizza, there was a 15 minute wait for the pizza so my wife and I decided to look around, and found Wang's. we went in and ordered, i must say the food is inexpensive and not cheap because the quality is really good. One part of the kitchen has a window where you can see the dumplings being freshly made. Note: the wonton come with 10 pieces, we already tried 2 before I decided to take a picture. We are definitely coming back for more!

featured_reviews.review_id: Fast service, efficient, everything you would expect at a Chinese food hole in the wall place.  Food is good and prices are fairly low compared to other similar places. Must have the XLBs. We also had the pan fried buns which were good, the fried porkchop rice was good.

featured_reviews.review_id: Arrived on a Sat evening and there was about a 20-30 min wait. Even though this place is very popular, I've been to other places that serve Chinese noodle dishes that are just as good at a similar price point. Don't get me wrong, the food was good, but for how busy and popular the place was, I expected slightly better. All in all, good food, but not mind blowing in which I would frequently patronize the place.

featured_reviews.review_id:
My family only waited about 5 minutes for a table on a weekday lunch. As soon as you get seated they give you menus and tea. Make sure you bring cash, cash only restaurant.

Soup dumplings were amazing! I have had zhajiang mian before and didn't like it but the one from here was really good. I also know a lot of people who like dan-dan noodles and they were indeed good but I found a bug in it and it turned me off. While eating the wait for tables grew with multiple people waiting and lined up outside.

featured_reviews.review_id: By far the best soup dumplings I have ever had! I always have to order another order because they are that good! You also know it's gonna be good when you can see them make them the dumplings right in front of you! I have been here many times already and their food does not disappoint. I got the Steamed Pork Buns (Xiao Long Bao/Soup Dumplings), Pan Fried Pork Buns, Pan Fried Dumplings and Beef Roll! I would recommend everything because it was really affordable and yummy. The soup from the Steamed and Fried Pork Buns was really flavourful! The Pan Fried Dumplings had a lot of filling and isn't like other dumplings I've had at other restaurants (which are sometimes frozen). You have to get the Beef Roll, I love the amount of meat, cucumbers and sauce there is in it! Another thing I like is how they have chili oil and vinegar at the table for you! I can't wait to come back and try their noodles and wontons,unfortunately it was too hot for that today.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Everything that I have tried here were amazing except for their dan-dan noodle which seemed a bit ordinary to me.

My favourite dish that I ordered would be their beef roll. Since their menu didn't have any images nor descriptions, I was left to imagine what this beef roll might be and surprisingly, it tasted amazing. I didn't expect it to be fried and if I didn't know it, the taste actually reminded me of peking duck.

This place accepts cash only so make sure to have cash on hand.
